ubuntu_linpeas_download.png ‚Äì Ubuntu retrieving linpeas.sh successfully

ubuntu_linpeas_initial_output.png ‚Äì initial scan execution confirmation (not full output)

üîç Outcome

Confirmed successful transfer of a real escalation enumerator

Demonstrated repeatable ingress transfer pattern

Began initial privilege escalation surface assessment

Personal Note

Privilege escalation looks much more complex when the tool output is right in front of you rather than in a diagram or tutorial.
Today felt like the first honest step into understanding how attackers move beyond access and begin shaping control.
